<abstract><t>The MPLS source routing paradigm provides path control for both intra- and inter- Autonomous System (AS) traffic.  For Intra-AS path control, protocols like RSVP-TE and CR-LDP are utilized.  This documents outlines how MPLS routers may use the BGP labeled unicast protocol (BGP-LU) for doing traffic-engineering on inter-AS links as outlined in [I-D.filsfils-spring-segment-routing-central-epe].</t></abstract>

